Package com.bakdata.dedupe.similarity

Class CachingSimilarity<T,​I>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bakdata.dedupe.similarity.CachingSimilarity<T,​I>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the record
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SimilarityMeasure<T>
    public final class CachingSimilarity<T,​I>
extends java.lang.Object
implements SimilarityMeasure<T>
    A light-weight caching layer over SimilarityMeasure to allow implementations to repeatedly calculate expensive similarities without implementing a cache on their own.

      • equality

        public static <T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>> CachingSimilarity<T,​T> equality​(SimilarityMeasure<T> measure)
        Creates a cache based on the object equality; that is, the cache triggers if two equal instances are compared.

        If the object does not implement a proper equals(Object), this method is effectively the same as identity(SimilarityMeasure).

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the record
        Returns:
        a cache based on the object equality

        public double getNonNullSimilarity​(@NonNull
                                   T left,
                                   @NonNull
                                   T right,
                                   @NonNull
                                   @NonNull SimilarityContext context)
        Description copied from interface: SimilarityMeasure
        Calculates the similarity of the left and right value.

        Note that some similarities are non-commutative, so that the order of the parameters matters.

        Specified by:
        getNonNullSimilarity in interface SimilarityMeasure<T>
        Parameters:
        left - the left element for which the similarity should be calculated.
        right - the right element for which the similarity should be calculated.
        context - the context of the comparison.
        Returns:
        the similarity [0; 1] or SimilarityMeasure.unknown() if no comparison can be performed (for example if left or right are null).
